Package: VolClusR
Title: Quantitative Regime Terminal
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Piyush", "Verma", , "piyushv24@iitk.ac.in", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A high-performance quantitative framework for identifying latent 
    market regimes in financial time series. The package utilizes a fast C++ 
    backend to extract rolling OHLCV features, including variance, Parkinson 
    volatility, and EWMA volatility shocks. It implements Principal Component 
    Analysis (PCA) for feature decorrelation followed by the 
    Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm via Gaussian Mixture Models (GMM) 
    to cluster market states. Includes an interactive Shiny dashboard for 
    visualizing transition matrices, return densities, and regime-switching 
    timelines.
